Vulva (Fig. 4
A-D
): Epigynum weakly sclerotized, covered with short setae (Fig. 4
A-B
), with a membranous scape posterior-mesially (Fig. 4C). Scape blunt, rugose. Spermathecae small and egg-shaped, strongly sclerotized, set far anterior from epigastric furrow (Fig. 4B). Membranous copulatory ducts wrapped long, spiral fertilization ducts (Fig. 4
C-D
